<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-07-05T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-07-05T09:00:00-05:00" n="257" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Dodd, William Edward/29:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Germany (<persName type="from">Gordon</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-05T10:00:00-04:00">July
                                        5, 1933—10 a.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>83. The procedure outlined in your No. 116 of July 1, 1 p.m. appears
                                satisfactory.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>[Ambassador Dodd assumed charge of the Embassy on July 14, 1933.
                                    He was received by President von Hindenburg on August 30. (123
                                    Dodd, William E./36, 45.)]</p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>